Description: Fix rdpecam camera never producing frames (first-frame sws deadlock)
 The CVE-2026-24677 fix (upstream d2d4f449, backported to this Debian source as
 channels-rdpecam-ensure-sws-context-size-matches-CVE-2026-24677.patch) added a
 guard at the very top of ecam_encoder_compress_h264():
 .
     if (!ecam_sws_valid(stream))
         return FALSE;
 .
 but stream->sws is created lazily by the only caller of
 ecam_init_sws_context(), which sits *later in this same function*. On the first
 captured frame stream->sws is always NULL, so ecam_sws_valid() returns FALSE and
 the function bails out before it can reach the line that would create the sws
 context. sws therefore stays NULL forever and every frame is dropped
 ("Frame drop or error in ecam_encoder_compress"): the camera enumerates into the
 server and streaming starts, but no SampleResponse is ever sent, so the remote
 side shows a permanently black image and times out.
 .
 This breaks every camera whose frames need libswscale conversion (MJPG and all
 raw YUV/RGB formats) on FreeRDP builds carrying the CVE fix but predating the
 upstream freerdp_video_context encoder rewrite. Upstream only escaped the
 deadlock via that rewrite, which is far too large to backport onto 3.15.0.
 .
 Remove the premature top guard. The genuine security property it was meant to
 add — the sws context must match the current media-type dimensions before
 sws_scale runs — is already enforced by ecam_init_sws_context(), which is called
 immediately before sws_scale() and recreates the context on any dimension
 change (that is the actual substance of the CVE fix and is left untouched).
Author: Slime OS <dev@mulai.com>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-07-17
--- a/channels/rdpecam/client/encoding.c
+++ b/channels/rdpecam/client/encoding.c
@@ -328,9 +328,6 @@ static BOOL ecam_encoder_compress_h264(C
 	CAM_MEDIA_FORMAT inputFormat = streamInputFormat(stream);
 	enum AVPixelFormat pixFormat = AV_PIX_FMT_NONE;

-	if (!ecam_sws_valid(stream))
-		return FALSE;
-
 #if defined(WITH_INPUT_FORMAT_H264)
 	if (inputFormat == CAM_MEDIA_FORMAT_MJPG_H264)
 	{
